social_posts.post_text: Working on myself everyday that’s all that matter !🤝🏾

December 13th is always a very special day to me … 4 years ago today my life completely changed❤️ blessed to be able to say I’m healthy and blessed to be able to return to the sport that I love to play ❤️❤️ these days were not fun at all, spending a year recovering and dealing with pain! I can live to say I fought and made it through ❤️❤️❤️

The former LSU Tiger Shareef O’Neal is a new age power forward with lots of upside. 

  Shaq’s Son has continued to show flashes of his fluid jump shot, athleticism and defensive IQ. Shareef currently plays for the G League Ignite along with others stars such as Scoot Henderson and Sidy Cissoko. O’Neal is a 6’10 solid power forward that has lots of untapped potential and the strength to belong in the NBA. He runs in transition very well and has sneaky leaping ability with a good touch around the rim. On the opposing side of the ball, O’Neal has good timing as he jumps to block shots and is able to guard multiple positions on the floor.

Really happy to see Shareef O’Neal thriving after open heart surgery nearly derailed his career. The 6’10” forward has been a key member off the bench for @gleagueignite. He’s averaging 5.8 points (66.7% FG) in only 11.0 minutes so far this season. 🙏 @shareefoneal 

Check out his highlights! He runs the floor well, is extremely athletic, and has a really nice touch on his jumper. Wishing him the best as he continues on his basketball journey.
